    <!--Block 1 Start-->
    <div class="section position-relative bg-level-1 light-bg-content">
        <div class="section service-section">
            <div class="r-container">
                <div class="row row-cols-lg-1 row-cols-1">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-xs-12 col-md-8 pe-lg-5  order-second">
                        <div class="info-para">
                            <div class="header-block">
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    The Department of Metabolic Health typically offers a range of services aimed at diagnosing, treating, and managing conditions related to metabolism and metabolic disorders. Some of the services that may be offered in a Department of Metabolic Health include:
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section position-relative bg-level-1 light-bg-content">
        <div class="section service-section">
            <div class="r-container">
                <div class="row row-cols-lg-1 row-cols-1">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-xs-12 col-md-8 pe-lg-5  order-second">
                        <div class="info-para">
                            <div class="header-block">
                                <ui>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                        <strong> Comprehensive metabolic assessments: </strong>Evaluation of metabolic health through blood tests, physical examinations, and other diagnostic assessments to identify risk factors and underlying conditions.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                        <strong>Diabetes management: </strong>Comprehensive care for individuals with diabetes, including medication management, blood sugar monitoring, dietary counseling, and lifestyle modifications.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                        <strong>Obesity management: </strong>Weight management programs, nutritional counseling, exercise plans, and behavioral therapy to help individuals achieve and maintain a healthy weight.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                        <strong>Nutritional counseling: </strong>Individualized meal planning, dietary guidance, and education on healthy eating habits to support metabolic health and manage conditions like diabetes and obesity.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                        <strong>Exercise counseling and fitness programs: </strong>Guidance on appropriate physical activity, exercise routines, and fitness plans tailored to individual needs and goals.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                        <strong>Hormone imbalance treatment: </strong>Evaluation and management of hormonal imbalances that can affect metabolism and overall health, such as thyroid disorders or polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS).
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                        <strong>Metabolic syndrome management: </strong>Comprehensive care for individuals with metabolic syndrome, including interventions to address high blood pressure, high cholesterol, insulin resistance, and abdominal obesity.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                        <strong>Cardiovascular risk assessment and management: </strong>Evaluation of cardiovascular risk factors associated with metabolic disorders, such as high cholesterol and high blood pressure, and interventions to reduce the risk of heart disease.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                        <strong>Genetic counseling and testing: </strong>Assessment of genetic factors influencing metabolic health and personalized counseling on genetic risks, inheritance patterns, and potential interventions.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                        <strong>Research and clinical trials: </strong> Participation in research studies and clinical trials focused on advancing understanding and treatment options for metabolic disorders, offering patients access to cutting-edge therapies and interventions.
                                </p>
                                 </ui>
